tbh, I understood that just a month or so back in time. Being a metalhead and riffing/shredding ARR seemed so small. But now since I've reached my saturation period ARR  Songs insiper me. I've been trying to find chords to learn to play them.
No wonder they call him the new age Ilayaraja. ARR is a Mind Stone definitely.
Such sheer brilliance with just following a very easy chord progression which makes you want to hear it OVER  & OVER & OVER again.

snippet.textDisplay: Love the tune if freed from the stupid theological existentialist argument introduced in the lyrics by Valee. You are to find your own meanings in your lives than bestowing it upon on a supernatural hypothetical entity. It also doesn't make your life’s purpose anyway more respectable or meaningful. If some groups of aliens created you in a parallel universe to use the energy generated by your body's exothermic reactions to wash their dirty laundry your birth doesn’t suddenly become more meaningful or it purpose doesn't become anyway more respectable to you or anyone else other than the planner. The same way if suppose if a lone women decided to give birth to a child thinking the child will love her back unconditionally thereafter, that satisfies the purpose of the mother and not the child.

snippet.textDisplay:
His father must be so proud watching AR from up there.....
He composed Roja soundtrack when he was only 24....
That's unbelievable...
Even Thiruda Thiruda, Bombay, Indian, Dil se, VTV, are out of this world....I can understand only a little bit of Tamil but AR's music cannot be restricted by languages....it's actually the tune, the instruments, the composition, the feel and concept....I couldn't believe when some people in UK walked out of his concert because they wanted songs in Hindi only ...! And the same people say repeatedly that music is a universal language! Haha...
They should also know that the songs which they call Hindi songs, are actually in Urdu language which makes them so beautiful....if they were in pure Hindi no one would have loved them so much...Hindi is also really beautiful but the songs won't be compatible enough...
Please respect all language and ethnicities....
Long live ARR...
Cheers!

snippet.textDisplay: "பச்சக்கரு யாவும்" எனபதற்குப்பதிலாக "பச்சக்கரு ஏதும்" என கவிஞர் வாலி எழுதியிருக்கவேண்டும்... "யாவும்" இட்டால், அதில் ஏதோ சில கருக்கள் பாவக்கருக்களாய் இருந்திருக்குமோ, ஏன்ற ஐயத்தோடே எழுதியதாய் உள்ளது.... "ஏதும்/எதுவும்" இட்டிருந்தால், ஒரு பச்சக்கருவும் பாவக்கருவாய் இருக்கமுடியாது என்று வந்திருக்கும், அது தான் உண்மையும்கூட... - தாசெ
